Building a Docker image from Dockerfile
Note:
▪To build a Docker image from a .jar file
(Spring Boot or Java app), the Dockerfile
will be as follows:
✓Write Dockerfile (screenshot)
✓After having the Dockerfile, run the
image build command: docker build
-t myapp:1.0 Explanation:
✓ docker build: image build command
✓ -t myapp:1.0: attach a tag to the image
(name is myapp, version 1.0)
✓ .: dot (.) ~ build context, meaning Docker
takes the Dockerfile in the current
directory# Use JDK runtime (only need JRE if not building in the
container)
FROM openjdk:17 -jdk-slim
# Set the working directory in the container
WORKDIR /app
# Copy the jar file from the host machine to the
container
COPY myapp.jar app.jar
# Open the application port (e.g., 8080)
EXPOSE 8080
# Command to run when the container starts
ENTRYPOINT ["java", " -jar", "app.jar"]

