3. Docker Compose
❑Modern applications rarely operate independently, often
requiring dependent services such as databases or APIs. ▪Docker Compose allows defining and managing multiple
containers in the same application. ▪Docker Compose uses a YAML format configuration file to
describe the services, volumes, and networks that make up
the application
oThat is, instead of running each complex docker run ... command, we only need to write a docker -compose.yml
file describing the services (applications), then use the
command: docker compose up
o→ Docker will automatically build, create a network, and
launch all containers. Thus: Docker Compose = Managing multi -container applications
(Microservices, Database + Backend + Frontend). University of Information Technology and
Communications

3. Docker Compose
❑Docker Compose is available in Docker Desktop, we can check with the command:
docker compose version
University of Information Technology and
