3. Docker Compose – Usage Process
University of Information Technology and
Communications1. Create a docker -compose.yml file to define the services. 2. Execute Docker compose to start the containers described in the YAML configuration file,
run the docker -compose up -d command in the directory containing the file
▪ The –d option runs the containers in detached mode, background mode. ▪ You can verify the running containers with the docker ps command, or through Docker Desktop
2. Container lifecycle management:
▪Stop: docker compose down
▪View log: docker compose logs –f
▪Restart: docker compose restart

